<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2639] remove random juggling in tests, add -Dtests.seed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2639</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Since we added newIndexWriterConfig/newDirectory, etc, a lot of tests are juggling randoms around.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead this patch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;changes it so LuceneTestCase&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;J4&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; manage the random.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;allow you to set -Dtests.seed=23432432432 to reproduce a test, rather than editing the code&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;removes random arguments from newIndexWriterConfig, newDirectory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I want to do this before looking at doing things like newField so we can vary term vectors, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also fixed the solr contrib builds so they arent hiding the exceptions i noted in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2002&quot; title=&quot;improve build/tests&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2002&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
